text: GURA READ THIS. Here's a trick for VERY quick xp in minecraft: make a furnace with a hopper underneath connecting to a chest. Place a switch on the furnace and cook/smelt things in it for 15-20 minutes while allowing the items to exit into the chest through the hopper. After 15+ minutes, hit the switch to stop the items from entering the hopper. Begin taking the items one at a time from the furnace. This will give you a few lvls per item taken. The more items cook/smelt during the waiting time the better. This can also be done using a blast furnace or even a smoker. Same setup. I reccomend using coal blocks as the fuel as it doesn't need to be refilled nearly as often as individual coal or even lava buckets. You'll get to high xp levels quickly with this. Any gear with mending will be repaired with this by far faster than any other method. Just make sure you have the intended item equipped
